    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix protocol timer initialization in ULSCH HARQ processes\n\n### Summary\nThe ULSCH HARQ processes were not being properly initialized with explicit protocol state values when created by new_eNB_ulsch. While memset was setting fields to zero, critical state fields like status, round, and repetition counters should be explicitly initialized for protocol compliance. This could lead to undefined behavior in downstream procedures that depend on these values for timing management.\n\nThis fix ensures all HARQ process state fields are properly initialized at creation time.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_TRANSPORT/ulsch_decoding.c`: Added explicit initialization of HARQ process state fields in new_eNB_ulsch function including status=SCH_IDLE, round=0, rvidx=0, phich_active=0, phich_ACK=0, repetition_number=0, and total_number_of_repetitions=1. Updated clean_eNb_ulsch to maintain consistency.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain network conditions with high ULSCH retransmission rates, users may observe inconsistent HARQ timing behavior or unexpected PHICH handling. The issue manifests as sporadic decoding failures that correlate with improper HARQ state initialization rather than actual channel conditions.\n"
}